msgid "Soft deprecations"
msgstr ""

msgid "There are no plans to remove :term:`soft deprecated` APIs."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
":func:`re.match` and :meth:`re.Pattern.match` are now :term:`soft "
"deprecated` in favor of the new :func:`re.prefixmatch` and :meth:`re.Pattern."
"prefixmatch` APIs, which have been added as alternate, more explicit names. "
"These are intended to be used to alleviate confusion around what *match* "
"means by following the Zen of Python's *\"Explicit is better than "
"implicit\"* mantra. Most other language regular expression libraries use an "
"API named *match* to mean what Python has always called *search*."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"We **do not** plan to remove the older :func:`!match` name, as it has been "
"used in code for over 30 years. Code supporting older versions of Python "
"should continue to use :func:`!match`, while new code should prefer :func:`!"
"prefixmatch`. See :ref:`prefixmatch-vs-match`."
msgstr ""

